{
  "texts": [
    "First, this code includes the __init__() constructor method to inform the API key and the target model, if applicable.",
    "The following is the particular code snippet generated for OpenAI's ChatGPT broker class OpenAIService implementing PromptService (note that, by default, we set DALL-E 3 as the model for image generation, whereas we let the user indicate which text completion model they want to prompt):At runtime, the trait validation method would return a JSON array with the particular Boolean evaluation of each of the reinforced traits.For example, let us consider a prompt that requests a text about a new year beginning tomorrow, with lots of joy, which contains two traits that need to be reinforced: the response must be ironic, and it must also be written as song lyrics.prompt PromptToValidate \"This prompt is an example to be validated\" (): text core = \"Provide a text that describes a new year beginning tomorrow\", \"It is expected to be full of hope and happiness\", language-register(ironic)[reinforced] suffix = literary-style(song)[reinforced] language = English When we generated the custom code to query Ope-nAI's gpt-3.5-turbo and executed it on February 20th, 2024, we received the following response, which follows the structure of a song and covers the requested theme:Oh what a year it's gonna be, starting fresh tomorrow you'll see Full of hope and joy, no time for sorrow We'll dance with glee, embracing each new day Oh what a year, we'll shout \"Hooray!\"",
    "(...) Oh what a year it's gonna be So full of hope and positivity Let's seize the day, let's make it grand This new year's gonna be oh so grand.By validating that response immediately afterward using gpt-4-vision-preview, we received the following assessment: the validator model concluded that the first model's response was effectively written as a song, but failed to use an ironic tone.",
    "[{\"trait\": \"ironic\", \"valid\": false}, {\"trait\": \"song\", \"valid\": true}]To sum up, code generation greatly simplifies the validation of relevant properties about the assets generated by a prompt.",
    "Moreover, thanks to the multimodal capabilities of the validator model, it is possible to check properties in generated assets beyond text (e.g., images)."
  ]
}